<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="46" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,724,1159,1185]" box="[151,724,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,724,1159,1185]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,724,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
Key to the 
<collectingCountry box="[287,442,1159,1185]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[574,724,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[574,724,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">Betasyrphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1232,1407]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
Note that the males of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,604,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stuckenbergi">
<emphasis box="[421,604,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">B. stuckenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not yet known and therefore are not included in the key. However the very long antennae will presumably also be present in the male sex and key out correctly. Both species have a completely yellow face, while a large proportion of the other Afrotropical species have a dark knob or median vitta on the face. For more distinctive characters and separation of the Oriental and Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Syrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serarius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">B. serarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<tableCitation box="[299,379,1381,1407]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,239,588,612]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,639,1948]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 1. Diagnostic characters of Betasyrphus keiseri sp. n., B. serarius (Wiedemann) and B. stuckenbergi (Keiser)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF636625FFBA2469FF171601190ED611" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" tableUuid="DF636625FFBA2469FF171601190ED611">
Tab. 
<number box="[357,373,1381,1407]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="46" type="key">
